## 1. Architectural Hardening Checklist (Evidence‑Based)

| Area | Recommended Action | AWS Reference |
|------|--------------------|---------------|
| **Network Segmentation** | • Place compute nodes (EC2) in **private subnets** only. <br>• Use **Security Group** rules that allow inbound traffic **only from the ELB** and **TransitGateway** as needed. <br>• Deploy a **bastion host** in a separate public subnet for admin SSH, protected by **AWS SSM Session Manager** (no inbound SSH). | <https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/VPC_Security.html> |
| **Identity & Access Management** | • Replace static access keys with **IAM Roles** and **Instance Profiles**. <br>• Enable **IAM Access Analyzer** and **IAM Credential Report**. <br>• Enforce **MFA** and **password policy** for all IAM users. | <https://docs.aws.amazon.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/access_policies.html> |
| **Data Protection** | • Encrypt **S3** and **EFS** with **KMS‑managed keys**. <br>• Enable **S3 Object Lock** for immutable research data. <br>• Use **TLS 1.2+** for all data in transit (ELB, S3 V4 signatures). | <https://docs.aws.amazon.com/kms/latest/developerguide/overview.html> |
| **Logging & Monitoring** | • Turn on **CloudTrail (multi‑region, log file integrity)**. <br>• Forward logs to **Amazon CloudWatch Logs** and enable **Insight** queries for anomalous activity. <br>• Deploy **Amazon GuardDuty** and **AWS Security Hub** for continuous threat detection. | <https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cloudtrail/latest/userguide/cloudtrail-create-and-update-a-trail.html> |
| **Resilience & DoS Protection** | • Enable **AWS Shield Standard** (automatic) and consider **Shield Advanced** for higher‑value workloads. <br>• Attach **AWS WAF** to the ELB with rate‑based rules. <br>• Use **Auto Scaling** with **target tracking** to absorb traffic spikes. | <https://docs.aws.amazon.com/waf/latest/developerguide/waf-chapter.html> |
| **Compliance & Auditing** | • Use **AWS Config** with managed rules (`s3-bucket-public-read-prohibited`, `ec2-instance-no-public-ip`, `kms-cmk-not-rotated`). <br>• Periodically run **AWS Security Hub** standards (CIS AWS Foundations, PCI DSS). | <https://docs.aws.amazon.com/config/latest/developerguide/evaluate-config.html> |
| **Least‑Privilege Service Roles** | • Create distinct IAM roles: <br> • `HPCComputeRole` – permissions: `ec2:Describe*`, `s3:GetObject`, `kms:Decrypt` on specific resources. <br> • `SageMakerHyperPodRole` – permissions limited to the SageMaker job’s S3 bucket and KMS key. <br> • `EFSAccessRole` – `elasticfilesystem:ClientMount`, `ClientWrite` on the specific file system. | <https://docs.aws.amazon.com/sagemaker/latest/dg/security-iam.html> |
| **Secure Bootstrapping** | • Use **EC2 Image Builder** to bake AMIs with **OS hardening** (CIS Benchmarks). <br>• Sign the AMI with **AWS Signer** and enforce **Launch Template** validation. | <https://aws.amazon.com/image-builder/> |
| **Secret Management** | • Store any runtime secrets (e.g., DB passwords) in **AWS Secrets Manager** or **Parameter Store (SecureString)**, accessed via IAM role. | <https://docs.aws.amazon.com/secretsmanager/latest/userguide/intro.html> |

