## 2. Sample Secure IAM Policy Snippets (Illustrative Only)

> **Note:** The policies below are **minimal examples** that follow the principle of least privilege. They are **not** full production policies; adapt resource ARNs, conditions, and actions to your exact workload.

### 2.1 HPC Compute Instance Role (`HPCComputeRole`)

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowReadOnlyS3Data",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject",
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::hpc-data-bucket",
        "arn:aws:s3:::hpc-data-bucket/*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "Sid": "DecryptKMSForData",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "kms:Decrypt",
        "kms:GenerateDataKey"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:kms:us-east-1:123456789012:key/abcd1234-ef56-7890-abcd-1234567890ab",
      "Condition": {
        "StringEquals": {
          "kms:EncryptionContext:Purpose": "HPC-Job"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "Sid": "EFSClientAccess",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "elasticfilesystem:ClientMount",
        "elasticfilesystem:ClientWrite"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:elasticfilesystem:us-east-1:123456789012:file-system/fs-0123456789abcdef0"
    },
    {
      "Sid": "CloudWatchMetrics",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "cloudwatch:PutMetricData"
      ],
      "Resource": "*",
      "Condition": {
        "StringEquals": {
          "cloudwatch:namespace": "HPC/Cluster"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### 2.2 SageMaker HyperPod Role (`SageMakerHyperPodRole`)

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "S3JobArtifacts",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:PutObject",
        "s3:GetObject",
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::hpc-job-artifacts",
        "arn:aws:s3:::hpc-job-artifacts/*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "Sid": "KMSJobKey",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "kms:Encrypt",
        "kms:Decrypt",
        "kms:GenerateDataKey"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:kms:us-east-1:123456789012:key/efgh5678-ijkl-9012-mnop-34567890qrst",
      "Condition": {
        "StringEquals": {
          "kms:EncryptionContext:JobId": "${aws:userid}"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

*Both policies should be attached via **IAM Role** to the respective service (EC2 launch template, SageMaker notebook/job).*

